25|$|Under {{the rules}} for {{distribution}} of estates without a will (the <b>Intestacy</b> Rules), where a child under 18 would inherit or a life interest would arise, the Court or District Probate Registry would normally appoint {{a minimum of two}} administrators. On some estates, even under an intestate, it is not clear who are the next-of-kin, and probate research may be required to find the entitled beneficiaries.|$|E
