50|$|An {{adopted child}} is deemed, for all purposes, {{to be the}} {{legitimate}} child of its adoptive parent. An order of adoption terminates all rights and obligations existing between the child and its natural parents (and their relatives). It follows that an adopted child inherits upon the <b>intestacy</b> of its adoptive parents and their relatives, but not upon the <b>intestacy</b> of its natural parents and their relatives.|$|E
